			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">(OOC - another repost, wanted all my old here before I started posting my new stories)
<br />

<br />
Theren and Sheren grew up closer than any siblings. It was rare to find them separated, even at night when they were put to sleep in their separate beds; one of the twins would move to the others bed. It was always an equal sharing, one night Theren would move, the next Sheren. 
<br />

<br />
But as they grew there was one startling difference in them. Sheren was blessed with the greatest of magic’s. Even at a young age the necromancers and shadow knights would watch her work the spells her teachers taught and smile, knowing that one day she would be as strong, if not stronger than her Father. But Theren showed no signs of magic. She was a beauty to watch with a blade in her hand, the sword and her formed together moving so swiftly and smoothly they looked as one weapon forged under Innoruk’s own hand. 
<br />

<br />
As we all know, the magic’s in Neriak are strong and the Teir’dal find strength in the gifts of magic from Innoruk. As they developed Sheren was held in high regard by the people of Neriak and by her family, while Theren was pushed slowly back and away from the sister she cared about more than anything. 
<br />

<br />
Sheren felt bad that she had such a gift and Theren had no magic, so she would take time to the temple and pray to Innoruk that he would grant some of her power to her sister. And when she would return to Theren she would talk of dreams she had where the two sisters grew into the finest disciples of Innoruk’s power that their rave had ever seen. In her dreams she saw herself as a wizard that faced dragons in their lair, while her sister moved towards them, a blade in each hand shining with the power of their God Innoruk. Theren would smile and hug her sister, knowing that they had a great future as long as they had each other.
<br />

<br />
But Innoruk and his people had other plans for the twins. When they reached the adolescence they were told to make the choices of their paths for the future. The casters guilds all came to visit Sheren over the course of a week. Many vied for her attention, promising power and gifts and the finest training available to a Teri’dal. Meanwhile two simple notes came for Theren, one from the warrior’s guild and one from the rogues. Treanani took Theren aside and talked of the paths of the warrior and rogue so she could make her choice easily, but even she could tell of his disappointment in her failure to follow him into the realm of the shadow knight. 
<br />

<br />
On the day Sheren was to make her choice she wanted time alone with her sister. In their rooms she took the matching swords they were given as children down off their stands and handed Theren her armor. “I need to think and the best way to do that is not to think.” 
<br />

<br />
Theren looked at her, a bit of jealousy glowing in her eyes, “Are you saying fighters don’t think?”
<br />

<br />
“Not at all, but I have so many choices and none have to do with swords and brutal acts,“ Sheren’s voice trailed off as she realized how she sounded, “Well I mean that I need to do something that has nothing to do with magic to help me release this stress.” She put on the armor that barely fit her anymore and walked for the arena. 
<br />

<br />
Sighing, Theren carefully strapped her perfectly fitted armor in place and took her sword in hand, following her sister out the door. She hated the fact that magic was so important to her family and that Innoruk would bring her into a family that thought this way. She felt the magic in her blade as she fought and saw no difference between her talent and Sheren’s, but her parents and those around her did not share those views. 
<br />

<br />
As they reached the arena many thoughts ran through each of their minds as the warmed up. Their Father had always taught them how to prepare for battle and no steps were missed. From limbering up to clearing all thoughts from their minds they prepared to face their opponents. 
<br />

<br />
Facing each other they made a swift salute and moved towards each other. Blades clashed and Sheren struck first blood, she moved across and brought a glancing blow to Theren’s hip. Theren felt the strike and danced away, minimizing the damage done by moving with the blade. The nick made in a small crease of her armor would be healed by night fall. But she was not about to be outdone in this art, her forte, her domain. Theren struck quickly as Sheren moved past, blocking down the blade and then striking up piercing lightly into Sheren’s arm. 
<br />

<br />
Sheren gasped and struck out at Theren, this fight was already more intense than most of their matches in the past. Slowly she became aware that her parents and others were watching from around them and she wanted them to see the beauty and power Theren held in her heart. She stepped back smiling and said snidely, “Not bad for a warrior.” 
<br />

<br />
Theren looked surprised; her sister knew how important fighting was to her and never held the attitudes of her family about the talent of her blade. She clenched her jaw and stepped back, “You do well yourself for a magical child.” They moved towards each other again and as Sheren struck Theren riposted and smacked her blade across Sheren’s thigh as she moved past.
<br />

<br />
Sheren knew that this was her chance to show everyone her sister’s greatness. She lunged forward and struck at Theren, but Theren eluded her blade and blocked the attack. Sheren knew if she could only get Theren to stop holding back they all would see. She instantly turned and engaged Theren again, forcing Theren back a step. 
<br />

<br />
Theren countered and stepped away a look of confusion crossing her face as Sheren laughed at her. “Come now warrior; show me what you’ve got.” Theren blinked and got tired of the game and started to turn away. But Sheren could not loose this opportunity and she yelled as she charged Theren’s back.
<br />

<br />
Taking a step to the side Theren cried out and turned, parrying Sheren’s attack, but at that moment Sheren’s blade broke and the point of Theren’s sword drove deeply into her side. Grabbing Sheren and holding her close she lowered her to the arena floor. Sheren smiled up at her as people ran into the arena, “Nice fighting Sis.” Theren had tears in her eyes as Sheren shuddered and sighed. 
<br />

<br />
Sarilella, their Mother kneeled next to Sheren. Theren turned to her, “Heal her!” 
<br />

<br />
“I can’t, it is too late.” Sarilella looked at Sheren in disgust, “Why wouldn’t she use magic. She is one of the strongest students in Neriak. A waste to die without using her greatest talent.”
<br />

<br />
“Mother, resurrect her, Lord Innoruk has given you the power, I will make sure she never touches a blade again. I need my sister.” Her skin tinting softly in pain and anger she grabbed her mother’s shoulders, but her Mother stood.
<br />

<br />
“Innoruk only saves those who use his powers wisely, your sister turned from his gifts and I will not waste my powers on an ungrateful child.” Sarilella turned from her children and looked to her husband with a demanding look. His face was torn between anger and confusion, he rounded on Theren.
<br />

<br />
“How could you do this to your sister? You know that her skills are not like yours, she was never gifted with the strength to wield a blade.” He screamed at Theren as she kneeled next to her sister.
<br />

<br />
Tears started to form in the corners of her eyes, “It was an accident. Her blade broke. We have always sparred. You know that.” But as she spoke her turned and put an arm around Sarilella’s shoulders. Theren’s eyes moved to the faces around her, looking for help, pleading for an answer.
<br />

<br />
The Head Cleric walked down to the floor and looked over the body laying there. “Sarilella has spoken Innoruk’s will; we shall all obey our Lord and Master.”
<br />

<br />
“WHAT?” Theren screamed and stood. “What kind of God acts against children killed in accidents? You all are his strongest supporters and you let one of your own die her in the dirt when you could help her! What wise person would do that?” Her eyes grew wide and she gestured wildly, “I will follow no God that asks that children be sacrificed, you all are pathetic cowards to not help my sister!”
<br />

<br />
At her words her Mother and father turned on her, “You will not blaspheme Innoruk in our presence! Go home now and we will discuss this once you have prayed to Innoruk and learned more of his will and his ways.” Her Mother’s eyes were wide with emotion, showing more pain at the words uttered against her God than the death of her child.
<br />

<br />
Theren stared incredulously at her parents and she walked past them. Stopping at the stairway to their home, she looked up at the symbol of Innoruk over the door. Realizing that she would not step foot in her home again she turned and walked off towards The Maidens Fancy.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=301723" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.thewolfe.net/images/sigs/Saffie_sigs/theren.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
